result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (3rd) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer, Penalty - Operating While under the Influence (3rd Offense)] and Operating w/ PAC (3rd) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer, Penalty - Operating While under the Influence (3rd Offense)]. The defendant was found guilty of OWI (3rd) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer, Penalty - Operating While under the Influence (3rd Offense)] and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (3rd) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer, Penalty - Operating While under the Influence (3rd Offense)] was dismissed by the court.

  • Tyson V. Vanderwilt Jr. was found guilty of OWI (3rd) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer, Penalty - Operating While under the Influence (3rd Offense)], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.
